<em>Cien veces y más</em><br />
<em>Erre ce dos</em></p>
<p>Thanks for your continued help testing out the latest versions of WordPress.</p>";}i:19;a:6:{s:5:"title";s:71:"HeroPress: Winners Announced for the WPShout Up and Running Scholarship";s:4:"guid";s:29:"https://heropress.com/?p=1864";s:4:"link";s:157:"https://heropress.com/winners-announced-wpshout-running-scholarship/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=winners-announced-wpshout-running-scholarship";s:11:"description";s:3425:"<img width="960" height="639" src="http://20094-presscdn.pagely.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/ipad-uandr-1-1024x682.png" class="attachment-large size-large wp-post-image" alt="Two hands holding an ipad so we can see the screen." /><p>After long hard thinking, the winners of the WPShout <a href="https://upandrunningwp.com/">Up and Running</a> Scholarship are announced!</p>
<ul>
<li><big>Elisabeth Klaar, Cambridge UK</big></li>
<li><big>Mohamed Hassan, Colombo, Sri Lanka</big></li>
<li><big>Bridget Mudzwiti, Harare, Zimbabwe</big></li>
<li><big>David Smith, Edmonton, Canada</big></li>
<li><big>Stephanie Meza, Bronx, NY, USA</big></li>
<li><big>Amy Koester, Gainesville, FL, USA</big></li>
<li><big>Birgit Olzem, Gerolstein, Germany</big></li>
<li><big>Ekene Olatunji, Lagos, Nigeria</big></li>
<li><big>Donum Theo, Yogyakarta, Indonesia</big></li>
<li><big>Jennifer Obiekwugo, Lagos State, Nigeria</big></li>
</ul>
<p>The winners will be contacted by WPShout with instructions on how to claim their scholarship. Congratulations to those who won!</p>
